er through a journey of how policymakers, organizations, and entrepreneurs shape the way implementers understand policies and translate them into action under ambiguous circumstances. The result is a complex picture of why some policies work in practice and others do not.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDecision making. 0aPolicy sciences. 0aPolitical planning. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Law. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 4aPublic Policy : Public Administration. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849360240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493602/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles